          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The self supporting thorium target of thickness",
                "2.5 mg/cm2 was covered with a 0.0025 cm thick",
                "aluminium catcher foil to collect the fission",
                "products."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 60 cc HPGe detector coupled to a PC-based",
                "4k MCA. The resolution of the detector was 1.75 keV",
                "at 1332 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The measured cross-section for a particular fission",
                "product is the cumulative cross-section for that mass",
                "chain up to the measured nuclide. In order to obtain",
                "the total cross-section for the mass chain, it is",
                "essential to correct the data for the fractional",
                "cumulative yields, using charge distribution",
                "systematics. In the absence of any literature data",
                "on the charge distribution for the system studied, the",
                "authors used the measured independent yields of the",
                "shielded antimony isotopes 122,124,125Sb to get an",
                "estimate of the charge distribution parameters viz.",
                "the most probable mass (Ap) and the width of the",
                "distribution (SA). These yields were fitted to a",
                "Gaussian; the resulting Ap and SA were 125.0 +-0.8",
                "and 2.2+-0.2 mass units respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
